                  <sealDesc>
                     <summary>Several relief-carved oval seal impressions of the emblem of former owner <persName>William Hook Morley</persName> appears on folios <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus>, <locus from="316b" to="316b">316b</locus>, <locus from="317a" to="317a">317a</locus>, and <locus from="390b" to="390b">390b</locus>.</summary>
                     <seal type="stamp" subtype="oval"><p>A fleur de lis crowns and protrudes from the mouth of a cat, encircled by a buckled belt bearing the phrase <q>WILLIAM • H • MORLEY • MIDDLE • TEMPLE</q>.</p>
                     <decoNote type="seal" subtype="dimensions"><p>
