                  <history>
                     <origin>Probably completed in <origPlace ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/00000">Someplace</origPlace> on <origDate calendar="#Gregorian" when="1820-07-04">4 July 1820</origDate>.
                     </origin>
                  <provenance><p>Formerly owned by <persName role="fmo aut" key="person_f829">Colonel Charles Joseph Doyle (1787-1848)</persName>, who served in India as Military Secretary to the Governor-General Lord Moira (later Marquess of Hastings) from 1813 to 1823, and a founder of the Royal Asiatic Society, to which he presented 18 Persian and 2 Arabic manuscripts in 1834, as per his signature on folio <locus from="390b" to="390b">390b.</locus>.
                  </p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p></p></provenance>
